  "prompt": "How many Knights of the Round Table were there?",
  "response": "The number of Knights of the Round Table can vary depending on the version of the Arthurian legend. In some accounts, there are as few as 12 knights, while in others, there may be as many as 150. The most commonly referred number in popular retellings of the legend is 12, including famous knights such as Sir Lancelot, Sir Gawain, Sir Percival, and Sir Galahad. However, Sir Thomas Malory's \"Le Morte d'Arthur\" describes 150 knights associated with King Arthur's Round Table. The exact number can vary based on the source.",
